        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 2:05PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 204 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Monroeton, or 7 miles southeast of Reidsville, moving north at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eden...
Reidsville...
Wentworth...
Mayfield...
Quick...
Harrisons Crossroads...
and Ruffin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
